result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Kaleb W. Wusterbarth was found guilty of OWI (3rd) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

records.addlTxt: Defendant called requesting to be paid for community service he is doing at Goodwill. Explained to defendant that we do not pay for community service but if he completes a community service agreement prior to performing service, that credit would be given against his fine. Defendant stated he completed community service and paid the application fee already and told me that I was looking at wrong person's record. Verified that he was calling about OWI-3rd case. Explained that we do not charge an application fee for community service agreements. Defendant then stated he would be in Clerk's office on Friday 12/9/16 to straighten this out after he got paid from Goodwill.
